# Shell scripts must keep LF endings in the repository.
#
# crm-backend/start.sh is the container entrypoint (railway.toml startCommand).
# With CRLF, Linux reads the shebang as "/bin/sh\r" and the container dies with
# "bad interpreter: /bin/sh^M" before anything listens on a port — which looks
# exactly like a healthcheck timeout and produces no application log at all.
#
# This repo is developed on Windows with core.autocrlf=true, so a checkout would
# otherwise hand the working copy CRLF and any tool that rewrites the file whole
# could commit it back that way.
*.sh text eol=lf
